  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA36-kiḷavi">iḵtiravukkuṟic ciṟaippuṟamākat tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said at the night tryst while he was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA36">
<l>            kuṟuṅkai yirumpulik kōḷva lēṟṟai</l>
<l>            pūnuta lirumpiṭi pulampat tākkit<app><note xml:lang="en"> line 2 in blank in G1+2</note></app></l> 
<l>            tāḻnīr naṉantalaip peruṅkaḷi ṟaṭūuṅ</l>
<l>            kallaka veṟpaṉ colliṟ ṟēṟi</l>
<l>            yāmen nalaṉiḻan taṉamē yāmat </l>
<l>            talarvāyp peṇṭi rampalō ṭoṉṟip</l>
<l>            puraiyi ṟīmoḻi payiṟṟiya vuraiyeṭut</l>
<l>            tāṉāk kauvait tākat</l>
<l>            tāṉeṉ ṉiḻantativ vaḻuṅka lūrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">Believing the word</l>
<l rend="indent2">of the man from the mountain with a mind of stone<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kallakam</term> can be taken to refer to HIM or to the mountain: "inside the rocks".</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent3">where the male of the short-handed big tiger, strong in</l>
<l rend="indent3">murdering, attacks [and] kills the big elephant bull</l>
<l rend="indent4">in the vast area of descending water,</l>
<l rend="indent3">for the female with [her] flower forehead to be lonely,</l>
<l>we lost our innocence.</l>
<l rend="indent4">At midnight,</l>
<l rend="indent">while [to me] it is unending affliction,</l>
<l rend="indent2">rousing comments that repeat ungenerous, fiery words,</l>
<l rend="indent2">gossip-mouthed women becoming one in [spreading] rumours,</l>
<l>what loss is it<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">āṉ</term> is here best understood as pronoun n.sg. referring back to the situation, i.e. subject of a nominal sentence, literally: "what [is] it that is lost?"</note> to this noisy village?</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
          </body>
